(uncountable) the People. Specifically the Mutsun people, a sub-group of Ohlone, natives of the present-day San Juan Bautista area of California.
1993, Ann Marie Sayers, The Story of Indian Canyon
Noso-N is central to the well-being of Ahmah (the People) as well as the natural and spiritual world we live in.

In breath, as it is in Spirit. Life for all living things.
